The first pattern of derepression identified ( type I ) consists of ectopic expression of cone <termsem="SO:0000704"> genes </term> in the vast majority of cells in the ONL .
These cells were also shown to coexpress all rod <termsem="SO:0000704"> genes </term> tested .
Consistent with the hybrid pattern of <termsem="SO:0000704"> gene </term> expression in these cells , electron microscopic analysis revealed them to be morphologically intermediate between normal rods and cones .
